1 exclusive control of the tenant and supplied by a direct public utility connection or
2 if the water or heat is unavailable due to supply failure by a public utility.
3 2. In case of noncompliance with the requirements of subdivisions b through f of
4 subsection 1, a reasonable time shall be allowed to remedy such noncompliance.
5 3. If the duty imposed by subdivision a of subsection 1 is greater than any duty imposed
6 by any other subdivision of that subsection, the landlord's duty shall be determined by
7 reference to subdivision a of subsection 1.
8 4. The landlord and tenant of a single-family residence may agree in writing that the
9 tenant perform the landlord's duties specified in subdivisions e and f of subsection 1
10 and also specified repairs, maintenance tasks, alterations, and remodeling, but only if
11 the transaction is entered into in good faith.
12 5. The landlord and tenant of any dwelling unit other than a single-family residence may
13 agree that the tenant is to perform specified repairs, maintenance tasks, alterations, or
14 remodeling only if:
15 a. The agreement of the parties is entered into in good faith and is set forth in a
16 separate writing signed by the parties and supported by adequate consideration.
17 b. The work is not necessary to cure noncompliance with subdivision e of
18 subsection 1.
19 c. The agreement does not diminish or affect the obligation of the landlord to other
20 tenants in the premises.
21 6. The landlord may not treat performance of the separate agreement described in
22 subsection 4 as a condition to any obligation or performance of any rental agreement.
23 7. As used in this section "reasonable heat" means between October first and Apri l
24 thirtieth, a temperature not less than sixty - eight degrees Fahrenheit [20 degrees
25 Celsius ] .
